div1.p:
71.
JOHN WILLIAM HOWLETT (25)
PLEADED GUILTY to
stealing a gold watch, the property of
Elizabeth Martin;
also to stealing a gold ring and other articles, the property of
John Strong;
also to stealing a pair of trousers and other articles, the property of
David Walsh;
also to forging and uttering a notice of withdrawal of £3 10s. from a deposit account;
also to stealing a Savings Bank book, the property of
H.M.'s Postmaster General.
Twelve months'hard labour. —

SMITH then PLEADED GUILTY to a previous conviction at Newington, on February 12th, 1896, and five other convictions of felony and misdemeanour were proved against him.
Eighteen months' hard labour;
EASTWELL,
Four months' hard labour;
KEEGAN,
Discharged on recognisances.

MR. CHARLES MATHEWS and MR. LEESE 
Prosecuted; 
MR. DOHERTY appeared for Zubesky; 
MR. BRAY for Obolnich, and MR. SIMPSON for Ziekel.
